Package: samplesizeBS
Type: Package
Title: Bayesian sample size in a decision-theoretic approach for the Birbaum-Saunders
Version: 0.1.2
Date: 2020-07-05
Author:  Eliador Costa[aut, cre] and Manoel Santos Neto [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Manoel Santos Neto <manoelferreira@uaest.ufcg.edu.br> and Eliardo Costa <eliardocosta@ccet.ufrn.br>
Description: Optimal Bayesian sample size for estimating the mean of the Birbaum-Saunders distribution. Also, this package includes the random generation of the joint posterior distribution of the BS/inverse-gamma model.
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2), LearnBayes, dplyr, ggplot2, magrittr, pbmcapply
License: GPL-3 + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.0
Suggests: testthat
